# Real-Time Socket.IO — Kitchen/POS Sync

## Event Namespace Convention
| Namespace | Subscribers | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/kitchen` | Kitchen display system | New orders, order status updates |
| `/pos` | POS terminals | Booking status, payment events |
| `/tables` | Frontend clients | Table availability changes |

## Backend — Emit AFTER Transaction Commits

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — emit outside the Prisma transaction
async createOrder(dto: CreateOrderDto) {
  const order = await this.prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
    // ... create order, update table status ...
    return newOrder;
  });

  // Emit only after transaction is committed
  this.kitchenGateway.server
    .to('/kitchen')
    .emit('order:new', { orderId: order.id, tableId: order.tableId, items: order.items });

  return order;
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG — emitting inside the transaction (may emit even if tx rolls back)
return this.prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  const order = await tx.order.create({ ... });
  this.kitchenGateway.server.emit('order:new', order); // dangerous
  return order;
});
```

## Frontend — Cache Update via Socket

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT — update TanStack Query cache from socket event
useEffect(() => {
  socket.on('table:status_changed', (payload: TableStatusPayload) => {
    queryClient.setQueryData(['tables', payload.tableId], (old: Table) => ({
      ...old,
      status: payload.status,
    }));
  });
  return () => { socket.off('table:status_changed'); };
}, [queryClient]);
```

## Rules
- ✅ Socket events must use `namespace:verb` naming (`order:new`, `table:status_changed`)
- ✅ All socket payloads must be typed with shared interfaces from `packages/shared`
- ❌ NEVER emit socket events inside a `$transaction` block
- ❌ NEVER mutate Zustand store directly from socket events — update TanStack Query cache instead
